Pakistan's military denies ceasefire violations in Kashmir, as tensions ease between India and Pakistan.
The first bus service between Indian and Pakistani zones of Kashmir will reunite families separated for decades.
Despite ongoing conflict, hopes for peace are rising with the resumption of talks and exchange of passenger lists for the bus service.
Kashmiri separatist leaders demand a seat at the negotiation table for lasting peace.
Indian Prime Minister Singh asserts Kashmir is integral to India, rejecting border redrawings.
Talks between India and Pakistan aim to find compromise on the longstanding Kashmir conflict, with potential for opening bus services after 57 years of division.
